article.headline: North Texas 86, Louisiana-Monroe 51
article.story: DENTON, Texas -- Tony Mitchell had 18 points, 15 rebounds and six blocks and Alzee Williams added 12 points as North Texas defeated Louisiana-Monroe 86-51 on Thursday night. Tyler Hall scored 11 points and Roger Franklin 10 as all 11 active players scored for the Mean Green (15-11, 8-5 Sun Belt). Fred Brown had 17 points and Marcelis Hansberry 10 for the Warhawks (2-24, 1-14), who lost their ninth straight. Mitchell's double-double was his fifth straight and ninth of the season. He has 27 blocked shots in his last five games. North Texas led 44-28 at the break and poured it on in the second half, holding Louisiana-Monroe to 23 points on 8 of 34 (23.5 percent) shooting en route to its 10th win in the last 11 meetings between the schools.
